Direct connection from ExpressRoute sites allows organizations to connect their on-premises infrastructure directly to Microsoft edge locations.

This provides a private and dedicated connection with high reliability.

For example, a company can establish a direct connection from its data center to an ExpressRoute location.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is enterprises handling sensitive workloads requiring secure and low-latency connections.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is large-scale data transfers between on-premises systems and Azure.

Direct connections ensure optimal performance and security.
